From: pasta-paul <paul@sunday.market>
Date: 2026-05-26
Subject: [PATCH] [Quantization] Refuse block-FP8 in MarlinFP8 can_implement

Marlin's per-channel scale layout cannot handle block-FP8 scales (shape
[N_blocks_n, N_blocks_k]) — the kernel TORCH_CHECKs b_scales.size(1) == size_n
at csrc/quantization/marlin/marlin.cu:701 and fails for any block-quantized
layer that reaches it.

Block-FP8 layers routinely reach Marlin when operators set
VLLM_TEST_FORCE_FP8_MARLIN=1 (required for NVFP4-MoE workloads on SM 12.0
in current upstream) because the dispatch in
_POSSIBLE_FP8_BLOCK_KERNELS[CUDA] places MarlinFP8 at priority 4 and the
env-var override marks it as supported on all SM ≥ 89.

The fix: have MarlinFP8.can_implement refuse layers whose activation_quant
is per-group (= block-quantized). The dispatcher then falls through to the
next supported kernel (TritonFp8BlockScaledMM, which handles block-FP8
correctly).

Reproducer: canada-quant/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-NVFP4-FP8-MTP on RTX PRO 6000
Blackwell with VLLM_TEST_FORCE_FP8_MARLIN=1 (required for NVFP4 MoE).
DSv4 compressor.fused_wqa_wkv ships FP8 block-128x128 scales — without
this patch, dispatcher picks MarlinFP8 → marlin.cu:701 fires
"b_scales dim 1 = 32 is not size_n = 1536".

After patch: dispatcher picks TritonFp8BlockScaledMMKernel; engine loads,
profile_run completes, model serves real completions.

Signed-off-by: pasta-paul <paul@sunday.market>
---
 .../kernels/linear/scaled_mm/marlin.py        | 17 ++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/vllm/model_executor/kernels/linear/scaled_mm/marlin.py b/vllm/model_executor/kernels/linear/scaled_mm/marlin.py
--- a/vllm/model_executor/kernels/linear/scaled_mm/marlin.py
+++ b/vllm/model_executor/kernels/linear/scaled_mm/marlin.py
@@ class MarlinFP8ScaledMMLinearKernel(ScaledMMLinearKernel):
     @classmethod
     def can_implement(cls, c: FP8ScaledMMLinearLayerConfig) -> tuple[bool, str | None]:
-        return True, None
+        # Marlin's per-channel scale layout cannot handle block-FP8 scales
+        # (shape [N_blocks_n, N_blocks_k]) → csrc/quantization/marlin/marlin.cu:701
+        # TORCH_CHECK b_scales.size(1) == size_n fires. Even when
+        # VLLM_TEST_FORCE_FP8_MARLIN=1 is set (which marks the kernel as
+        # supported on SM ≥ 89), block-FP8 attention layers like DSv4
+        # compressor.fused_wqa_wkv must fall back to the block-FP8 Triton
+        # kernel further down the priority list.
+        try:
+            if c.activation_quant_key.scale.group_shape.is_per_group():
+                return False, (
+                    "MarlinFP8 cannot serve block-FP8 layers; falling through "
+                    "to TritonFp8BlockScaledMMKernel via the dispatcher."
+                )
+        except Exception:
+            pass
+        return True, None
